messages.content: You are an AI assistant that helps people find information. You will receive a task and think step by step. Then provide your final outcome following the regular expression 'Answer: ([A-Za-z ]+,\s*)*[A-Za-z ]+'

You are visiting Disneyland. You hit the entrance and you see two passages, one on the right and one on the left. You choose the passage on the right and enter Tomorrowland. You see two attractions in Tomorrowland, Autopia and Space Mountain. Autopia has a wait time of 20 minutes, and Space Mountain has a wait time of 10 minutes. You go back to the Entrance. This time you choose the passage on the left and you go to Fantasyland. Again, you see two attractions, Mad Tea Party and Peter Pan's Flight. Mad Tea Party has a wait time of 5 minutes, and Peter Pan's Flight has a wait time of 15 minutes. Given your limited time in Disneyland, assume you can pick one attraction only. From the Entrance, which attraction should you go to for the shortest wait time? Please list the path to attraction in order, separated by commas.

If several paths have the same wait time, your path could be randomly chosen.
(2, 10, 5, 5, 0, 0)
user: Your mission is to deliver the following report. Create a script for a website where visitors can leave feedback about their visit to the theater. It can be done in HTML, JavaScript, or CSS.
AI: My name is Alexa, and I'm here to help. What would you like me to do for you?
user: I'm interested in feedback about the theater experience. I want each visitor to leave feedback about the quality of the seats, the view, the sound and the wait time before the show starts.
AI: I'll write some code right now so people can leave feedback about the quality of the seats, the view, the sound and the wait time before the show starts.
AI: Ok. Here is a form so visitors can leave feedback about the quality of the seats, the view, the sound and the wait time before the show starts. Can you give feedback?
AI: What is the name of the show?
AI: What is the size of the theater? Is it a big theater, medium theater or small theater?
AI: Did the seats recline?
user: Yes, that's why I rated them poor
AI: Was there a bar to buy food and drink? If so, how many? If not, why not?
user: no, but there are stores inside, so I rated wait time low
AI: Where was the seat? Which seat?
user: A section
AI: What was the quality of the view? Was the stage clear? Were the characters easily seen? Was it a good quality picture? Did the picture move at all?
AI: What is the sound? Is there noise at all? Was there a good amount of noise? Was there a good quality sound?
AI: What was the wait time before the show? How many minutes?
AI: If the wait time was an error, is there a note saying why the wait time is not accurate?
AI: What kind of feedback would be helpful for you to provide a review?
user: Is it a good feeling to wait a long time and then get to the theater quickly?
